==English==

===Etymology===
First attested circa [[w:17th century|17th century]], alteration of [[huzzah]]. This is however questionable. Another plausible etymology is from mongolian war cry "Urra", which made its way to slavic languages as "Ura" (in 12-13 century) and later to Germanic languages: "hurra" in Germain, Danish, Swedish and Norwegian.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪ|-eɪ]]

===Interjection===
'''hooray''' ''or'' '''[[hurray]]''' ''or'' '''[[hurrah]]''' 
[[Category:Interjections]]

# Used to express [[approval]], [[joy]] or [[victory]].

